articles.title: Nuggets' Jamal Murray fined $100000 after throwing heat pack in Game 2 - Star Tribune
articles.description: Timberwolves coach Chris Finch called Jamal Murray's act "inexcusable" and "dangerous." Officials didn't see who threw the heat pack and added it would have been a technical foul if they had — not an ejection.
articles.content:
DENVER The NBA fined Nuggets guard Jamal Murray $100,000 but did not suspend him for throwing multiple objects onto the floor during the Timberwolves' Game 2 victory on Monday night.
